  "full_text": "Blobber\nDetails\nHealth\n3\nMove\n2\nSystems\nUnstable Growths\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nThrow a sticky\nblob\nthat will explode.\nThe\nBlobber\nis a rare\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nThe Blobber maintains a safe distance from mechs, attempting to attack by spawning\nBlobs\nonto any tile across from them, in the row or columns they can move in. Blobs always explode last in the attack order during the enemy turn they were spawned, and damage all adjacent tiles for 1.\nBlobbers are capped at one spawn per mission (alphas included) and cannot spawn on island 1, nor can it co-exist with the normal and alpha variants of the\nSpider\nand\nPlasmodia\n.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nBlobbers are annoying, as the blobs they shoot can divert you from the Blobber itself, so that you don't get an opportunity to kill it. In order to kill it and its blob in one turn, look for a pilot ability like\nSilica\n's and/or a Mech that can resolve two targets like the\nRocket Mech\n's artillery projectile and electric smoke. But don't prioritize it over other attacking Vek nor its Blob.\nWhile deploying your mechs, keep in mind that the Blobber will try to shoot his blob in explosion range of as many targets as possible (including buildings and mission objectives). Thus, it's possible to bait the Blobber into shooting at a space between two of your deployed Mechs, for example, freeing you from having to destroy or move the blob.\nA few examples of Mechs that are effective at destroying the Blob while hitting an enemy (be it the Blobber itself or another enemy) include:\nthe\nRocket Mech\n, which can position itself next to Blob and fire in the opposite direction to hit another target, letting the electric smoke behind dispose of the Blob.\nthe\nUnstable Mech\n, which can use Unstable Cannon's knockback to hit the Blob, while aiming at an enemy with the projectile.\nSee Also\n[\n]\nBlob\nv\n\u00b7\nd\n\u00b7\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n\u2022\nBlobber\n\u2022\nBurrower\n\u2022\nCentipede\n\u2022\nCrab\n\u2022\nDigger\n\u2022\nFirefly\n\u2022\nHornet\n\u2022\nLeaper\n\u2022\nScarab\n\u2022\nScorpion\n\u2022\nSpider\n\u2022\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n\u2022\nGastropod\n\u2022\nMosquito\n\u2022\nMoth\n\u2022\nPlasmodia\n\u2022\nStarfish\n\u2022\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n\u2022\nAlpha Blobber\n\u2022\nAlpha Burrower\n\u2022\nAlpha Centipede\n\u2022\nAlpha Crab\n\u2022\nAlpha Digger\n\u2022\nAlpha Firefly\n\u2022\nAlpha Hornet\n\u2022\nAlpha Leaper\n\u2022\nAlpha Scarab\n\u2022\nAlpha Scorpion\n\u2022\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n\u2022\nAlpha Gastropod\n\u2022\nAlpha Mosquito\n\u2022\nAlpha Moth\n\u2022\nAlpha Plasmodia\n\u2022\nAlpha Starfish\n\u2022\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n\u2022\nBlood Psion\n\u2022\nShell Psion\n\u2022\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n\u2022\nRaging Psion\n\u2022\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n\u2022\nAlpha Blob\n\u2022\nSpiderling Egg\n\u2022\nSpiderling\n\u2022\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n\u2022\nAlpha Spore\n\u2022\nVicious Spore\n\u2022\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n\u2022\nFirefly Leader\n\u2022\nHornet Leader\n\u2022\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) \u2022\nPsion Abomination\n\u2022\nScorpion Leader\n\u2022\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n\u2022\nBouncer Leader\n\u2022\nCentipede Leader\n\u2022\nCrab Leader\n\u2022\nGastropod Leader\n\u2022\nMosquito Leader\n\u2022\nPlasmodia Leader\n\u2022\nScarab Leader\n\u2022\nStarfish Leader\n\u2022\nTumblebug Leader",
